description:

name: Grand 4-Level Painted Lady Victorian with Parking
description:
Our 6000SF Painted Lady with a Walk Score of 97 is located in the heart of happening Lower Pacific Heights! Walking distance to Fillmore Jazz District, Golden Gate Park and Golden Gate Bridge!

Parking for 4 cars: 1 in garage, 3 adjacent to garage

The space
Enjoy the grandeur of this restored 19th century San Francisco Edwardian Mansion. Your friends and family will be enveloped by the scale of rooms and the 11 foot high ceilings. There is room for your entire group to enjoy cocktails and relaxation in the grand living room. Play your favorite music via the Sonos app on your mobile device. There are additional large living areas in the penthouse and bottom floor suites including TV viewing areas and pool table. A stay in this home will add color and richness to your San Francisco experience!

Deck off kitchen can be used as smoking area.

Guest access

host_about: Outgoing, fun-loving, longterm SF residents. I am originally from Germany and my husband is fluent in Spanish! We know the city inside/out!

name: Lovely, Unique Home Near Everything
description:
A Queen Anne cottage built in 1890, it looks small from our quiet, tree-lined street, but it has 3 stories and plenty of room. Each room is cozy and stylish, including a room designed for children. Has all amenities and everything you might need is close by.

See below for information about our rigorous cleaning and disinfecting protocol.

The space
Our lovely Queen Anne home dates from 1890, though its grown in size and sophistication over the years, as has the neighborhood. It's located on a quiet, treelined little street, one lane, one-way and only one block long, but within steps of everything one could want: many different bus and metro lines, "The Wiggle" bike route, bars, cafes, stores, and Duboce Park, one of San Francisco's best. On Walk Score it rates 100 as both a "Walker's Paradise" and a "Rider's Paradise"; it's also rated 89 for cycling as "Very Bikeable (some hills, excellent lanes)".

neighborhood_overview: Our home is in the Lower Haight neighborhood but right on the border of the Duboce Triangle neighborhood, both charming in different ways.  See the guide for recommendations on the many restaurants and bars that are just a few steps from our quiet little block.
host_about: I'm a 57 yo environmental lawyer; my wife Almudena, 48, is an international human rights lawyer from Spain, and our son Diego is 8. Ours is an engaged, dynamic, and athletic family.  We ride our bikes everywhere.
amenities: Smart speakers with Sonos Bluetooth sound system

name: Home in the Castro
description:
SPECIAL NOTE JULY AUGUST SEPTEMBER: If you are interested in renting the house for several weeks or months during the months of July, August and September please inquire (no matter what calendar says about availability)!!

The Castro is one of San Francisco's historic neighborhoods. Original Victorian homes populate tree lined streets and cafes, restaurants, shops, and nightclubs are all a stone's throw away.

The space
Old world charm meets modern comfort at this home in the heart of the Castro, one of San Francisco's most vibrant neighborhoods.

This is a two-story home. Upstairs, you'll find three private bedrooms to retreat to at the end of a full day. The master bedroom features a king sized bed and city views. The second bedroom is equipped with a queen sized bed and opens to a private balcony overlooking the backyard garden. The third bedroom has a full sized bed.

We have locked a few cabinets and the garage for our private b
host_about: I am 51 years old, originally from Ohio but I have lived in San Francisco for over 26 years, and lived in this 3 story Victorian for 19 years. My partner Marco is from Rome, Italy. We have a 4 year old chihuahua/dachshund/papillon mix named Carly. I try to travel to Italy every year. I also have a home in Provincetown, MA. where I can be found part of the summer.

name: ⭐️ Luxury 3BR Home w/Views, Steam Room on Roof Deck ⭐️
description:
Enjoy luxury-level San Francisco living in this gorgeous, well-appointed house with free and easy street parking (read the signs) in the Twin Peaks neighborhood of San Francisco.

Grab a bottle of wine from the full-sized wine cooler in the kitchen, take in the amazing views from the roof deck and BBQ with a few friends. Have a steam session in the rooftop sauna with a sparkling night-time view, then curl up by the working fireplace, the cable TV with Netflix, or in luxury bedding in a king-sized bed.

Smart-thermostat automatic heated flooring, high ceilings, a working fireplace, luxury linens, a serenity space Master Bath, Kiehl's bath products, beautiful furnishings and modern appliances (including a washer and dryer in a dedicated laundry room), and lots of space to spread out and relax, all provide a higher level of comfort for your business or vacation travel. Shopping, dining and activities are only a few minutes from your door.

The space<

We are an international family, Cameron is from Brisbane, Australia and Daniela is from Munich, Germany. Max (5), Anna (4) and James (1.5) were all born in San Francisco and so was our dog Angel.

We love to travel and are excited to share our house with people who can enjoy San Francisco and our home as much as we do.

description:
Grill and relax in the shaded backyard, complete with fountain, of this magnificent home. Entertain or just sit back on the elegant neo-classical furniture inside and enjoy the fine artwork. Numerous refined touches include Carrara marble tops.

neighborhood_overview: The Marina is the liveliest, sunniest neighborhood in San Francisco, complete with beach access, world-class restaurants, yacht clubs, bars, coffee shops, movie theaters, and shopping galore. It's also close to the infamous Alcatraz island.
host_about: We are an active family that enjoys skiing in Lake Tahoe in the winter and playing tennis & traveling in the summer. I am a native Californian and graduated from UCLA. I have worked in Technology for the past 20 years, currently in downtown San Francisco.

name: Cole Valley Casa
description:
The Cole Valley Casa is a home I love! Built in 1906, mid block on a beautiful street off of Cole. Sleeps at least 6 people comfortably, large common areas for cooking, eating, visiting. Superb location- muni train only 2 blocks which will easily take you one way to the beach other way Union Square, downtown, Embarcadero and Giants Stadium. Walkability fantastic- Cole Valley shops and restaurants, UCSF, Haight Street, Golden Gate Park, wonderful grocers all within 10 minute walk or less.

The space
Cole Valley Casa is a home built in 1906, for rent by the week or monthly. The house has 3 bedrooms very comfortable for 3 couples plus - 2 queen beds, one sofa bed and a single. Two bedrooms are downstairs and one bedroom is upstairs. The upstairs room is a large room with a queen, a single and a sitting area with a sofa and chair. The upstairs can be used for sleeping 4 adults or a sleeping room for children. There is a roof deck with nice views up to Sutro To
neighborhood_overview:
Location- House is located mid block on a beautiful side street off of Cole Street very quiet! Two short blocks to muni N line which will take you downtown, Embarcadero, Giants Games or west to the beach. Also buses take you to the Marina or Mission etc. Though it’s not necessary to leave Cole Valley, many restaurants, cafes, bars, within walking distance. Also excellent groceries within walking distance; Whole Foods and excellent local grocers. You can walk over the hill to the Castor District in about 20 minutes or Haight Street in 10 minutes. Golden Gate Park is a 10 minute walk to the west.

Back yard makes this a good home base with children and pets.
host_about:
I'm a women who loves the country life and the city life.  Currently I have a home in San Francisco and rent out the country home in Sebastopol where I raised my children.  We built the Casa in 1983. 

 I'm a retired healthcare executive and specialized in home infusion therapy.  I have a degree in nursing.  I love animals and gardens.  I have travelled a lot in the last few years and spent a couple of years living in Guatemala, it was a wonderful experience.  

I love gardens- flowering perennials mixed with edibles.  I'm learning a new climate in San Francisco, much milder and new plants from Sebastopol.

Two miles from Moscone Convention Center, AT&T Park and countless restaurants and attractions.

DREAMFORCE NOTE: We can rearrange beds if you want two twins in each of the four bedrooms.

Home is walking distance to Golden Gate Bridge, Crissy beach, 3 high end shopping streets with restaurants and designer shops. A bus line at the end of the block can quickly get you downtown, Union Square, Fisherman's Wharf, etc.

Quiet street, great light, impeccable and spacious. 4 bedrooms/3.5 baths all on same floor.

See reviews from our previous guests.

The space
1904 Victorian rebuilt from the studs 4 years ago. It is a superb base in San Francisco for a quick holiday or an extended stay. The house itself is over 3000 square feet / 300 m2 and has 4 parking spaces (2 garaged, two outside) as well as a small back yard both of which are rare in San Francisco. host_about: From San Francisco work in business development at a mobile advertising startup.  Father of 3 great kids.

description:
Supremely furnished with mid-century modern trappings and refined artwork, this listing is an oasis for those wishing to explore SF and retire to something peaceful. Lounge, wetbar, rainfall shower, and a dedicated solid wood desk are just few of the amenities you can enjoy.

Based in the medially-located Sunnyside, you can go to:
- Golden Gate Bridge in 20 minutes,
- Golden Gate Park in 15 minutes,
- Chase Center in 10 minutes
- Or Union Square in 15 minutes.

The space
At our two story property based on an open floor plan and decorated with a mid-century modern furnishings, you can relax surrounded by warm tones with hints of blue to balance out the atmosphere.

Admire statement pieces as you work your way from the living room to the kitchen to your bedroom. Work on the the bar seating on the island or cook your meal on the gallery. Both are clad in beautiful Caesarstone quartz. In the mornings, you can enjoy various s
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is family oriented. Peaceful in the early mornings and at night. A Safeway that is open late is located on the block. Enjoy walking or biking in the hills that occupy Westwood, Monterey Heights, St. Francis Woods. You can also shop at the mom and pop stores lined along West Portal, Glen Park, and Ocean Avenue. Stonestown Galleria is a 10 minute drive away for shopping.

Oh finding parking takes an average of 1 minute to find. A rarity for San Francisco.

Plus Ultra. Further Beyond. 

Tutor, Coach, Investor, Part-Time Athlete, Coffee Connoisseur, Car Enthusiast, Photography Dabbler.

description:
Traditional Victorian in front, modern open floor plan in back. It all started with an 1890's stick style Victorian which underwent a major renovation beginning in 2009 by local architect James Hill. We're perched on a hill with 10 ft. windows and a deck overlooking the city. A 5 min. stroll brings you to the cafes and restaurants of 24th Street in Noe Valley, and about 15-20 min. walk to Valencia Street in the Mission District.

host_about: Born and raised in California, lived and worked in 12 countries in Asia / Europe. Traveled the world for a year with my wife. 100+ Airbnb stays and now hosting for the first time.

name: NEW LISTING! San Francisco Retreat Just Steps from Golden Gate Park and Ocean Beach!
description:
This is a warm, sophisticated home located in the Inner Sunset district of San Francisco. The house is steps from famous Golden Gate Park, the Museum of Modern Art, The world famous Japanese tea garden, Stow lake and still only one mile from Ocean beach! Located across the street from Starbucks.

The space
We are just steps to major stores, all recognized banks and services ,restaurants, bakeries bars... etc. All of this is a 2 min walk. The Home is situated in a vibrant neighborhood known as the inner sunset.

A charming old-world home gone modern. It features two bedrooms and two full bathrooms. An old world fireplace cradles the expansive open plan living area. The high ceilings give the area a real sense of space and air. Large rear Redwood deck along with a large fully fenced and enclosed backyard.

Property can comfortably sleep 2 guests in each bedroom and 3 in the living room if need be for a total of 7.

name: Newly Remodeled Loft in Lower Nob Hill
description:
Beautiful loft located on lower Nob Hill.  Cable Car, Union Square and Fisherman's Wharf are within walking distance.  Great international restaurants, shopping and theaters close by.  There is a private garage, and the house has easy access to Marin and Chrissy Field.

This is a brick building from 1914 that has been updated for the 21st Century.  This property was home to renowned interior designer Robert Hutchinson for nearly 50 years.  Mr. Hutchinson bought the property in 1961 and turned the first floor into his studio, while he lived upstairs.  The second story, where you will be staying, has seen many designs over the years.  Once, it was Chinese red, another time it was black.  When it was featured in Architectural Digest in 1986, the walls and ceilings were tan and the flat was filled with tribal art from around the globe.  There will be vintage magazines on site that show the projects of Mr.
